# Interactively run through all test conditions, computes and renders all html
src=lapply(seq_along(cond), function(i) {
  cur_cond=names(cond)[[i]]
  print(cond[[cur_cond]][2])
  print(cond[[cur_cond]][1])
  knit_expand(file="./RuvChild.Rmd", cond1=cond[[cur_cond]][2], cond2=cond[[cur_cond]][1], K=K)
})

knit_res=paste(knit_child(text=unlist(src)), collapse="\n")
# Subset data based on treatment and condition pair
cond1="CTR"
cond2="JC4"

Differential Expression Results: JC4 vs CTR

KK="2"
KK <- as.numeric(KK)
suffix <- paste0(cond2, "_vs_", cond1)
dir.create(suffix)
# sampleData clean-up ----------------------------------------------------------
### Only get the row.names (sample) of investigating condition. 
sampleData <- sampleParent[c(which(sampleParent$condition==cond1),
                             which(sampleParent$condition==cond2)), ]
### Only get the colnames (covariate) of investigating variances. 
sampleData <- sampleData[, which(covParent$take_nottake==1)]
### Relevel condition so that it's TREATMENT vs CONTROL 
sampleData$condition <- droplevels(sampleData$condition)
sampleData$condition <- factor(sampleData$condition, levels=c(cond1, cond2))

# countData clean-up -----------------------------------------------------------
countData <- countParent[, row.names(sampleData)]

# covData clean-up -------------------------------------------------------------
covData <- covParent[which(covParent$take_nottake==1),]
if (all.equal(colnames(sampleData), as.character(covData$covariate)) != TRUE) {
  error1 <- "Error: Check sampleData and covData. They do not have the same covariate strings."
  print(colnames(sampleData))
  print(covData$covariate)}

if (all.equal(colnames(countData), row.names(sampleData)) != TRUE) {error2 <- "Error: Check countData and sampleData. They do not have the same column names and row names"
  } else {
    # Make DESeq object 
    dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData=countData, colData=sampleData, design= ~ condition)
    dds$condition <- factor(dds$condition, levels=c(cond1, cond2))
    dds <- DESeq(dds, parallel=TRUE)
  } #-End else

if(exists("error1")) { print(error1)}
if(exists("error2")) { print(error2)}

DESeq2 First-Pass

DESeq2 was used to perform data normalization and differential expression analysis. This is the first pass to create a set of genes whose expressions were not differentially expressed between 2 investigated groups (adj p-val > 0.75). These genes, refered to as empirical control genes, are then used for downstream RUVseq analysis (Removal of Unwanted Variation).

# Write results of DESeq2 first pass to a text file 
res <- results(dds)
res <- lfcShrink(dds, res=res, coef = resultsNames(dds)[2])
res <- as.data.frame(res)
res <- res[order(res$padj), ]
write.table(res, file=paste0(suffix, "/", "FirstPass_deSeq2_", cond2, "_vs_", cond1, ".txt"), quote=FALSE, sep="\t", col.names=NA)
res1 <- res
# Get negative genes for empirical control. In this case we want those genes whose padj values are more than 0.75
empirical <- row.names(res)[which(res$padj > 0.75)]

The number of empirical control genes used in this experiment is: 22117

# Write out empirical control genes 
filename <- paste0("EmpiricalControlGenes", cond2, "_vs_", cond1, ".txt")
writeLines(empirical, sep="\n", con=filename)

# Run RUVSeq (RUVg)
set <- betweenLaneNormalization(as.matrix(countData), which="upper")
setG <- RUVg(set, empirical, k=KK)

DESeq2 Second-Pass with RUVseq

sampleDataW <-cbind(sampleData, setG$W)
ddsW <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = countData, colData = sampleDataW, design = ~ condition)
ddsW$condition <- factor(ddsW$condition, levels = c(cond1, cond2))

### compile formula for DESeq2 based on number of K:
      form_string <- ""
      for (w in 1:KK) {
        if (w == KK) {
          form_string <- paste(form_string, "W_", w, sep = "")
        } else {
          form_string <- paste(form_string, "W_", w, " + ", sep = "")
        } # end else
      } # end for
      
      design(ddsW) <- formula(paste("~", form_string, " + condition", sep = ""))

ddsW <- DESeq(ddsW, parallel = TRUE)
res <- results(ddsW)
coef <- paste0("condition_", cond2, "_vs_", cond1)
res <- lfcShrink(ddsW, res=res, coef = coef)
res.summary <- res
# Write results of DESeq2 second pass to a text file 
res <- res[order(res$padj), ]
res <- as.data.frame(res)
write.table(res, file=paste0(suffix, "/", "RUV_deSeq2_", cond2, "_vs_", cond1, ".txt"), quote=FALSE, sep="\t", col.names=NA)

Venn Diagram Showing the Compostion of Differentially Expressed Genes Across Comparisons

##### How many genes are differentially expressed between conditions
####### Cut-off: |FC| > 0 and padj < 0.01
# Read in differential expression results
files <- list.files("../RUV", "RUV_deSeq2", recursive = TRUE, full.names = TRUE)
dres <- list()
for ( file in files) {
  dres[[file]] <- read.table(file)
}
names(dres) <- gsub(".*RUV_deSeq2_", "", names(dres))
names(dres) <- gsub("\\.txt", "", names(dres))
dres_ordered <- lapply(dres, function(x) x[order(x$padj),])

up <- lapply(dres_ordered, function(x) row.names(x)[which(x$log2FoldChange > 0 & x$padj < 0.01)])
down <- lapply(dres_ordered, function(x) row.names(x)[which(x$log2FoldChange < 0 & x$padj < 0.01)])
dys <- lapply(dres_ordered, function(x) row.names(x)[which(abs(x$log2FoldChange) > 0 & x$padj < 0.01)])

# Function to extract signif GO as a data frame
my_enrichr.f <- function(enrichR_res){
  X <- plyr::ldply(enrichR_res, rbind)
  X <- X[order(X$Adjusted.P.value), ]
  signif_X <- X[which(X$Adjusted.P.value < 0.05),]
  X$Overlap <- gsub("\\/", "_", X$Overlap)
  return(signif_X)
}

# Pathways that are significantly enriched (adjp < 0.05) for each up and down-regulated gene list. 
pway.up <- my_enrichr.f(enriched.up)
pway.down <- my_enrichr.f(enriched.down)

#####---------------------------EDGES
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
pway.up <- pway.up[order(pway.up$Adjusted.P.value),]
pway.down <- pway.down[order(pway.down$Adjusted.P.value),]
pway.df <- rbind(pway.up[1:10, c(2,10)], pway.down[1:10,c(2,10)])
df <- data.frame(Source = character(), Target = character())
for (i in 1:nrow(pway.df)) {
  goi <- pway.df$Genes[i]
  goi <- strsplit(goi, ";")[[1]]
  tmp.df <- data.frame(Source = goi, Target = rep(pway.df$Term[i], length(goi)))
  df <- rbind(df, tmp.df)
}
# Remove GO term ID 
df$Target <- gsub("\\ \\(GO\\:.*", "", df$Target)
#####---------------------------NODES
df2 <- data.frame(id = c(df$Source, df$Target))
df2$label <- c(rep("Gene", nrow(df)), rep("Pathway", nrow(df))) 
row.names(df2) <- NULL
df2 <- df2[!duplicated(df2), ]
df2$early <- rep(0, nrow(df2))
df2$late <- rep(0, nrow(df2))
df2$overall <- rep(0, nrow(df2))
for (i in 1:nrow(df2)) {
  df2$early[i] <- round(dres[[3]][df2$id[i],]$log2FoldChange,1)
  df2$late[i] <- round(dres[[2]][df2$id[i],]$log2FoldChange,1)
  df2$overall[i] <- round(dres[[1]][df2$id[i],]$log2FoldChange,1)
}
df2$direction <- rep(0, nrow(df2))
df2$direction <- ifelse(df2$id %in% signif.up, "up", 0 )
df2$direction <- ifelse(df2$id %in% signif.down, "down", df2$direction)

# RUVg with empirical control genes set as the combination of all genes from all comparison 
# Run RUVSeq (RUVg) on all samples 
empirical <- c(readLines("EmpiricalControlGenesJC14_vs_CTR.txt"),
               readLines("EmpiricalControlGenesJC14_vs_JC4.txt"), 
               readLines("EmpiricalControlGenesJC4_vs_CTR.txt"))
empirical <- unique(empirical)
countData <- read.table("./data/countData.txt")
colnames(countData) <- c("Set1_D00","Set1_D04","Set1_D14","Set2_D00","Set2_D04","Set2_D14","Set3_D00","Set3_D04","Set3_D14")
set <- betweenLaneNormalization(as.matrix(countData), which="upper")
setG <- RUVg(set, empirical, k=2)
# Corrected counts 
rawCounts <- setG$normalizedCounts
# Import length info
gl <- read.table("./data/gene_lengths.txt", row.names=1, header=T)
gl <- gl[order(row.names(gl)),, drop=FALSE ]
rawCounts <- rawCounts[order(row.names(rawCounts)),]
tpmRUV <- data.frame(row.names=row.names(rawCounts))

for (i in 1:9) {
  geneLength <- merge(rawCounts[,i, drop=FALSE], gl, by="row.names")
  colnames(geneLength) <- c("Gene", "Expression", "Length")
  # Calculate TPM
  geneLength$RPK <- (geneLength$Expression/geneLength$Length)
  scalingBy <- sum(geneLength$RPK)/1000000
  geneLength$TPM <- geneLength$RPK/scalingBy
  
  # Make data frame to export
  tpmRUV[, i] <- geneLength$TPM
}
colnames(tpmRUV) <- colnames(rawCounts)

annot_colors <- list(Early=c("grey60", NA), Late=c("grey60", NA), Overall=c("grey60", NA), Day=main_color)
names(annot_colors[[1]]) <- c("Early", "None")
names(annot_colors[[2]]) <- c("Late", "None")
names(annot_colors[[3]]) <- c("Overall", "None")
names(annot_colors[[4]]) <- c("Day 00", "Day 04", "Day 14")
# Rearrange samples 
sample.v <- c(1,4,7,2,5,8,3,6,9)
###########################################
for (i in 0:4) {
  goi <- mod$Id[mod$modularity_class == i]
  goi <- dys_ordered[dys_ordered %in% goi][1:20]
  # Top 20 of the dysregulated genes 
  datatoplot2 <- tpm[goi,]
  datatoplot2 <- datatoplot2[, sample.v]
  print(pheatmap(as.matrix(datatoplot2), annotation_col =  annotCol, annotation_row = annotRow2[goi,], annotation_colors = annot_colors,cluster_rows = T, cluster_cols = F, color = main_pal, border_color = NA, scale = "row", cellwidth = 10, cellheight = 8, show_rownames = TRUE, show_colnames = FALSE, clustering_method = "complete", treeheight_row = 0))
}
